text:
Werner Konrad Graf von (count of) Moltke (24 May 1936 – 29/30 July 2019) was a German decathlete. He won a European title in 1966 and finished second in 1962. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics, but failed to finish. He was born in Mühlhausen, Germany.
Von Moltke died on 29 or 30 July 2019 in Nieder-Olm, Germany at the age of 83.
